<chapter xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"  xml:id="chap_transformations_eigenvalues">
  <title>Eigenvalues of Linear Transformations</title>
  <introduction>
    <objectives>
      <introduction>
        <p>
          By the end of this section, you should be able to give precise and thorough answers to the
          questions listed below. You may want to keep these questions in mind to focus your thoughts as
          you complete the section.
        </p>
      </introduction>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <p>
            How, and under what conditions,
            do we define the eigenvalues and eigenvectors of a linear transformation?
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            How do we find eigenvalues and eigenvectors of a linear transformation?
            What important result provides that our method for doing so works?
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            What does it mean to diagonalize a linear transformation?
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            Under what conditions is a linear transformation diagonalizable?
          </p>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </objectives>
  </introduction>
